node.text:
For over 70 years, we have made it our mission to be the most trusted choice for a bride searching for her dream wedding dress 👰 From the moment you walk through our infamous glass doors, your experience with us is unlike anywhere else 🌎⁣
⁣
You’ll be greeted by our friendly staff, welcomed into our 35,000 square foot main salon, and paired with your knowledgeable bridal consultant ✨⁣You will also have access to the largest curated selection of wedding dresses in the country and a devoted staff of over 200 to help you every step of the way 🙌 ⁣
⁣
Ready to experience the magic of #Kleinfeld yourself? Tap the link in bio to book an appointment 💗

"At the tender age of 17-years-old, Aaron told me he was going to marry me. He found a bubble gum machine ring and placed it on my finger, but I brushed it off because we were just kids," said @_selenax4. 💍 Nonetheless, these high school sweethearts *always* knew that they were meant for one another. 👩‍❤️‍👨 ⁣
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⁣
After years of being a @sayyes_tlc fan, Selena's time came for her to go wedding dress shopping. "At first, I had my heart set on a specific @maggiesotterodesigns wedding dress that I had found in my hometown, but was unable to try it on in my size. I told my mom we had to book a trip to NYC so I could try the dress on at #Kleinfeld." 👰⁣
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⁣
While the dress didn't turn out to have the WOW factor Selena was looking for, her consultant Candace pulled another dress by Maggie Sottero for her to try. "Once I put the dress on in the fitting room, I knew this style was THE dress. I didn't want to take it off...it made me feel amazing." 🔥 To solidify her choice even more, Selena's mother brought her veil that she wore on her wedding day 25 years ago, and the details from the veil and Selena's dress were spot on. 🙌 l Photo @BonnieTurnerPhoto
